tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditionally Exempt / 16th qualifier from Qualifying Tournament, Money List 61-100
tourBios.carHigh: Member of the Web.com Tour in 1993, 1996-97 and 2000. Has not played regularly on Tour since the 2000 season. Member of PGA TOUR in 1990-91, 1994-95 and 1998-99. 2011: Missed the cut at the WNB Golf Classic in his only start. Made six starts on the PGA TOUR from 2000-2007 but did not make a cut. Made nine starts on the Web.com Tour from 2001-2011. 2000: Made the cut in six of 19 starts on the Web.com Tour. His best finish was a T12 at the Cleveland Open..Shot a final-round 71 to jump from 18th to a T5 at the 1999 Shell Houston Open, his best finish of the season. 1998: Enjoyed his best season on the PGA TOUR...His four top-10s matched his career total...Was 77th on the PGA TOUR money list with $401,440. 1998: Was within four shots of the lead after 54 holes at the Kemper Open. A final-round 73 was good for a T3 , matching his best career PGA TOUR finish. 1997: Flirted with golf history on the Web.com Tour, when he fired a final-round, 11- under-par 60 at St. Louis Golf Classic. 1996: Had conditional status, allowing him to play in only 16 events, making 10 cuts. His best finish was a T10 in Wichita Open. 1994: Was T6 at the U.S. Open. Earned $289,065, enabling him to retain playing privileges for first time in five tries with a 65th-place finish on money list. 1993: Winner of 1993 Bakersfield Open on the Web.com Tour, defeating Jim Furyk and Sonny Skinner in playoff...Successfully defended his Newport Classic title. 1992: Won the Texas State Open and the Newport Classic. 1988: Captured the Nevada State Open.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was a two-time American Junior Golf Association All American and was the 1983 Texas State Junior champion...Attended Nolan High School.
tourBios.personal: Instructors include Dan Stimple, Geoff Jones and Dan Whittaker...Biggest thrill in golf is shooting a 59 in the 2009 Texas State Open with his son Will caddying...Biggest thrill outside golf is the birth of his sons...Favorite courses he has played are Royal Melbourne GC and Pebble Beach GL...Never travels without his iPhone...Superstitions include never carrying a $50 bill and will not mark his ball with a nickel...Favorite college teams are the Arkansas Razorbacks and the TCU Horned Frogs, and his favorite pro teams are the Texas Rangers and Dallas Mavericks...Favorite TV show is "The Simpsons," and his top movies are "Blazing Saddles" and "Pulp Fiction." Enjoys listening to the Eagles and Jimmy Buffet...Favorite athletes to watch are Dirk Nowitski and Josh Hamilton...Favorite cities to visit are Paris, France, and Sydney, Austrailia...Favorite vacation spot is any city with a beach...Favorite gadgets are his iPhone and iPad...Favorite app is for weather...Keeps Clif Bars in his bag for a snack...Dream foursome would include his three sons...Supports St. Jude's.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was 1st in 1993 at the NIKE Bakersfield Open.
